    "Moreover, the dysregulation of specific groups of genes in cortico-cortical projection neurons has been found to correlate with the clinical severity of ASD, as expected [48].Oligodendrocytes are implicated in the pathogenesis of MS, a multifocal inflammatory disease affecting cortical areas [152].",
    "SnRNA-seq has demonstrated different functional states of oligodendrocyte subpopulations in MS tissue and has identified selectively vulnerable neuronal subpopulations, stressed oligodendrocytes, reactive astrocytes, and activated microglia associated with the progression of MS lesions [153,154].",
    "Overlapping transcriptional profiles between MS and other neurodegenerative diseases suggest shared mechanisms and potential therapeutic approaches [155].",
